data.chText: 一个名不见经传的德国诗人
他生于1650年前后，但身世不详。
data.enText: He was born around 1650 but his origins remain obscure.

data.chText: 我觉得她的讲座非常费解。
data.enText: I found her lecture very obscure.

data.chText: 他莫名其妙地没有如期露面。
data.enText: For some obscure reason , he failed to turn up.

data.chText: 他们让她无缘无故地担忧起来。
data.enText: They were making her feel obscurely worried (= for reasons that were difficult to understand) .
to make it difficult to see, hear or understand sth
The view was obscured by fog.

data.chText: 我们不能让枝节问题掩盖主要问题。
data.enText: We mustn't let these minor details obscure the main issue.

tr: make undecipherable or imperceptible by obscuring or concealing
reduce a vowel to a neutral one, such as a schwa

example: The stars are obscured by the clouds
the big elm tree obscures our view of the valley
an impulse to go off and fight certain obscure battles of his own spirit"-Anatole Broyar
their descriptions of human behavior become vague, dull, and unclear"- P.A.Soroki
vague...forms of speech...have so long passed for mysteries of science"- John Lock

tr: marked by difficulty of style or expression
example: much that was dark is now quite clear to me
those who do not appreciate Kafka's work say his style is obscure

tr: remote and separate physically or socially
example: existed over the centuries as a world apart
preserved because they inhabited a place apart"- W.H.Hudso
tiny isolated villages remote from centers of civilization
an unnoticeable cigarette burn on the carpet

value.def: If something or someone is obscure, they are unknown, or are known by only a few people.

example.ex: The origin of the custom is obscure...
example.tran: 这一习俗的起源鲜为人知。

example.ex: The hymn was written by an obscure Greek composer for the 1896 Athens Olympics.
example.tran: 这首赞歌是希腊一位名不见经传的作曲家为1896年的雅典奥运会创作的。

value.tran: 无名的；鲜为人知的；默默无闻的

value.def: Something that is obscure is difficult to understand or deal with, usually because it involves so many parts or details.

example.ex: The contracts are written in obscure language...
example.tran: 这些合同的语言晦涩难懂。
理查德的声明隐晦费解，真是丢人。

value.tran: （通常指因内容繁琐）晦涩的，费解的，难懂的

value.def: If one thing obscures another, it prevents it from being seen or heard properly.

example.ex: Trees obscured his vision; he couldn't see much of the Square's southern half...
example.tran: 树木遮挡了他的视线，南半广场的一大部分他都无法看清。

example.ex: One wall of the parliament building is now almost completely obscured by a huge banner.
example.tran: 议会大楼的一面墙现在几乎被一条巨型横幅完全盖住了。

value.def: To obscure something means to make it difficult to understand.

example.ex: ...the jargon that frequently obscures educational writing...
example.tran: 经常让普教著作变得艰深晦涩的术语

example.ex: This issue has been obscured by recent events.
example.tran: 最近发生的一些事件使这一问题变得混淆不清。
